        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 4:20PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 420 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
La Cienega, or 12 miles southwest of Santa Fe, moving southwest at
10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southwestern Santa Fe, Eldorado At Santa Fe, Cerrillos Hills State
Park, Los Cerrillos, La Cienega, Madrid, La Bajada and Pena Blanca.

This includes Interstate 25 between Mile Markers 262 and 276.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
